    {
      "id": "RQ-0067",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Defer retry warnings until runner recovery is exhausted",
      "description": "Retry admission and auto-revert paths log warnings during in-flight self-healing. Goal: collect retry diagnostics per attempt, keep in-flight logs at debug/trace, and emit ample redacted detail only on terminal failure or operator-visible recovery output.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "retry",
        "logging",
        "reliability"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/orchestration/core.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/retry_policy.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/orchestration/tests.rs",
        "make agent-ci"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/orchestration/core.rs:114-127 logs warn! when auto-revert before retry fails, even though retry/fallback logic may still succeed later.",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/execution/retry_policy.rs:31-39 logs warn! and skips retry when repo cleanliness probing fails; this is a terminal decision path but not attached to the final runner diagnostic surface.",
        "User focus requires hiding errors and warnings until all retries and self-healing are exhausted, then providing ample logging.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce a retry diagnostic accumulator for auto-revert and retry-admission failures.",
        "Downgrade in-flight retry/self-healing logs to debug unless no retry/fallback remains possible.",
        "Attach accumulated retry diagnostics to the final RunAbort/safeguard dump/operator message when recovery exhausts.",
        "Add tests that successful retry after an auto-revert warning path does not emit warning-level output and terminal failure includes collected diagnostics.",
        "Verify by running cargo test -p ralph runutil::execution and make agent-ci."
      ],
      "notes": [],
