      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Classify missing CLI binaries as cli_unavailable in machine errors",
      "description": "The machine contract defines a typed cli_unavailable code, but the classifier does not currently map common missing-binary/spawn failures to it. Goal: make app-side recovery typed and stable instead of falling through to Unknown or unrelated generic codes.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "machine",
        "typing",
        "macos"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/machine.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/error.rs",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIRecoveryClassifier.swift",
        "make agent-ci"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/machine.rs:57-69 defines MachineErrorCode::CliUnavailable.",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/error.rs:42-116 classifies task conflict, permission, queue, config, version, network, and resource-busy errors, but has no branch for command-not-found, executable missing, spawn ENOENT, or CLI unavailable failures.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced.",
        "Reproduction steps: force a machine subcommand path to use a missing executable/spawn failure and inspect the emitted MachineErrorDocument code."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add classifier predicates for no such file or directory, command not found, executable not found, spawn ENOENT, and bundled CLI unavailable phrases before generic parse/unknown branches.",
        "Return MachineErrorCode::CliUnavailable with a stable user-facing message and non-retryable flag unless the source is a transient resource-busy condition.",
        "Add Rust machine error tests and align RalphMac recovery classification if it currently relies on Unknown fallbacks.",
        "Verify by running cargo test -p ralph cli::machine::error and make agent-ci."
      ],
      "notes": [],
