        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/RetryIntegrationTests.swift",
        "make macos-test-contracts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace.swift:460-469 wires RetryProgressHandler to handleRetryMessage during retry attempts.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace.swift:486-495 only classifies RecoveryError and shows the recovery sheet after the final thrown error, which is correct terminal behavior.",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+GraphData.swift:35-37 builds 'Retrying load graph...' copy and apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+GraphData.swift:51-55 writes it into graphDataErrorMessage, the same field used for terminal failures.",
        "Command run: make agent-ci -> passed docs-only gate; no baseline CI blocker reproduced."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce separate non-error retry/progress state for repository loads, or keep progress internal unless the view has an explicit neutral status surface.",
        "Update graph/task/config/analytics load call sites so retry progress does not populate *ErrorMessage fields.",
        "Keep terminal failure classification unchanged and ensure final failure includes retry attempt count and last redacted error detail.",
        "Add RalphCore tests asserting transient retry progress does not set error-message properties and terminal failure still does.",
        "Verify by running the focused RalphCore retry tests or make macos-test-contracts, then make agent-ci."
      ],
